 ## Safety boundary
 
-JobSniffing discovers, scores, prepares, and tracks. It does not attempt universal auto-submission. A future submission adapter must be site-specific, dry-run-first, and must observe a confirmation signal before the state can become `submitted`.
+JobSniffing discovers, scores, prepares, fills, and tracks supported ATS applications. Browser adapters remain site-specific, dry-run-first, fail-closed, and may record `submitted` only after concrete confirmation evidence. Unsupported or uncertified flows remain manual.
 
